#: .uk.SS2_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_DESCRIPTION
msgid ""
"The Nemesis Mercenary is a fast-paced, short-range survivor, with the tools "
"to dominate any combat encounter - no matter the odds. \n"
"\n"
"<color=#CCD3E0>< ! > Splatter deals devastating damage at close range. Use "
"your other skills to close the distance.\n"
"\n"
"< ! > Use Cutthroat to interrupt attacks, or to redirect your dash towards "
"more enemies.\n"
"\n"
"< ! > Dispatch is a powerful mobility option in combat, and doesn't interrupt "
"your reload.\n"
"\n"
"< ! > Attack Vectors can be blinked to with no cooldown. This makes Exploit a "
"key skill in navigating intense situations."
msgstr ""

#: .uk.SS2_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_OUTRO_FLAVOR
msgid "..and so he left, with newfound purpose in every shell."
msgstr ""

#: .uk.SS2_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_OUTRO_FAILURE
msgid "..and so he vanished, with emptied munitions and an emptier heart."
msgstr ""
"...і він був стертий, зі спорожнілим боєзапасом та ще більш порожнім серцем."

#: .uk.SS2_NEMESIS_MERCENARY_LORE
msgid ""
"“Hey!“\n"
"\n"
"A figure slowly hobbled out from the sandy Martian dunes, tuning into Fort "
"Laughn's external communications. “Hey, mind letting me in? Dust out here is "
"killing me.“\n"
"\n"
"One of the stationed guards on the outer fence quipped back from a booth. "
"“...You got credentials, sir?“\n"
"\n"
"“Come on, you don't recognize me? Let me guess- new recruit? Something like "
"that?“ The figure continued walking nonchalantly toward the fence as a second "
"guard piped up. “Hold on. Is that Vantre?“ The guest laughed, still wandering "
"every-which-way as he came closer to the fence. “Guilty as charged. Thought "
"I'd stop by while I'm in the area. Say hey to some old comrades, maybe.“\n"
"\n"
"The guards paused, then, on a separate line, rang up their CO. “Commanding "
"Officer Byren, Vantre's at the outer fence. He appears non-threatening, which "
"is an immediate red flag. What're your orders?“\n"
"\n"
"Byren's scratchy, exasperated voice chirped back through the receiver. “Ugh, "
"damnit� Page the suppression crew. Make sure he's not trying anything, "
"alright? Keep him busy until you've got more people out there.“ The guard "
"relayed the order- “Get a crew out here. I'll make sure Vantre doesn't try "
"anything stupid.“ The recruit replied with a question: “Sure, but, uhh� "
"Where'd he go?“\n"
"\n"
"Sure enough, Vantre had vanished while the two were distracted, leaving "
"nothing but sparks in the air where he once stood. It took the entirety of "
"the fort's stationed force about ten minutes to figure out what was going on- "
"and they found out at about the same time they found their commanding officer "
"dead in his quarters, the back of his head blasted to smithereens."
msgstr ""

